  "prompt": "What do people do to not get bored in an MRI full body scan?",
  "response": "During an MRI scan, people try various methods to stay calm and avoid boredom:\n\n1. Mental strategies:\n- Meditation or deep breathing exercises\n- Counting or mental math\n- Reciting songs, poems, or prayers in their mind\n- Visualization techniques\n- Thinking about pleasant memories or future plans\n\n2. Communication with technician:\n- Some MRI machines have communication systems\n- You can request music or talk to the technician\n- Ask about the scan's progress\n\n3. Provided distractions:\n- Listening to music through provided headphones\n- Watching a movie or TV show on a screen\n- Podcast or audiobook\n\n4. Physical comfort:\n- Using a comfort cushion\n- Wearing comfortable clothing\n- Keeping eyes closed\n- Trying to relax and stay still\n\n5. Practical preparation:\n- Bring earplugs to reduce noise\n- Take prescribed anti-anxiety medication if recommended\n- Discuss anxiety with technician beforehand\n\n6. Coping techniques:\n- Practice relaxation techniques before the scan\n- Ask about sedation options if very anxious\n- Focus on steady breathing\n\nThe key is finding a method that helps you stay calm and still during the scan.",
